5.4.5 Practical Tips
--------------------

   • When to use sequential

        • Order truly matters (can't install before purchasing)
        • You're not sure what the next task will be until you complete
          the current one
        • The project is simple and you don't want to think about
          dependencies

   • When to use parallel

        • You have multiple people working on the project
        • Tasks are independent and could be done in any order
        • You want to optimize for speed
        • Clear what all tasks are upfront

   • Managing complexity

        • Start sequential, make parallel only when needed
        • Use areas of focus or tags to group related tasks
        • Keep task names clear and specific
        • Review stuck projects weekly to catch dependency issues

   • Modifying projects over time

        • Add tasks: Use "Add to existing project" when organizing new
          items
        • Change dependencies: Edit properties directly, then run
          fix-keywords command
        • Split tasks: Break down a task into sub-tasks, adjust
          dependencies
        • Merge tasks: Mark unnecessary tasks DONE or CNCL


