5.4.8 Troubleshooting Projects
------------------------------

   • Project is stuck (has TODO tasks but no NEXT)

     Run ‘M-x org-gtd-review-stuck-projects’ to find stuck projects.

     Common causes:
        • Circular dependency (A depends on B, B depends on A)
        • Missing FIRST_TASKS (project has no starting point)
        • All first tasks are DONE but dependencies not set up correctly

     Fix: Put point on project heading, run
     ‘org-gtd-projects-fix-todo-keywords-for-project-at-point’

   • Task should be NEXT but shows as TODO

     The dependency graph says it's blocked.  Check:
       1. What tasks are in its ORG_GTD_DEPENDS_ON?
       2. Are those tasks actually DONE?
       3. Did you forget to remove a dependency?

     Fix: Edit ORG_GTD_DEPENDS_ON property, run fix-keywords command.

   • Too many tasks are NEXT

     You probably have tasks that should have dependencies but don't.

     Fix: Add appropriate ORG_GTD_DEPENDS_ON properties to tasks that
     shouldn't start yet, run fix-keywords command.

     *See also*:
